chunks.html_content: A speed limiter centre installs or adjusts devices that limit how fast a vehicle can go.
chunks.plain_content:
Becoming a speed limiter centre
A speed limiter centre installs or adjusts devices that limit how fast a vehicle can go.

chunks.html_content: Usually, only existing vehicle dealerships will become a speed limiter centre.
chunks.plain_content:
Becoming a speed limiter centre
Usually, only existing vehicle dealerships will become a speed limiter centre.

chunks.html_content:
If you want to become a speed limiter centre, you’ll need to get either:

  • approval from the Driver and Vehicle Standards Agency (DVSA) to become an independent centre
  • sponsored by a DVSA approved vehicle or speed limiter maker
chunks.plain_content:
Becoming a speed limiter centre
If you want to become a speed limiter centre, you’ll need to get either:

  approval from the Driver and Vehicle Standards Agency (DVSA) to become an independent centre

  
sponsored by a DVSA approved vehicle or speed limiter maker

chunks.html_content: Fill in the application form and send it to DVSA.

chunks.html_content: DVSA will inspect your premises, facilities and staff before approving your speed limiter centre.
chunks.plain_content:
Becoming a speed limiter centre
Inspections
DVSA will inspect your premises, facilities and staff before approving your speed limiter centre.

chunks.html_content: You’ll receive an authorisation letter from DVSA if your independent speed limiter centre is approved.
chunks.plain_content:
Becoming a speed limiter centre
Approval
You’ll receive an authorisation letter from DVSA if your independent speed limiter centre is approved.

chunks.html_content:
You’ll need to be a sponsored vehicle dealership to become a sponsored speed limiter centre.

Sponsors are DVSA-approved makers or suppliers of either:

  • vehicles
  • speed limiters

Once approved, sponsors are able to approve vehicle dealerships they already work with that want to become speed limiter centres.
chunks.plain_content:
Becoming a speed limiter centre
Sponsors
You’ll need to be a sponsored vehicle dealership to become a sponsored speed limiter centre.
Sponsors are DVSA-approved makers or suppliers of either:

  vehicles
  speed limiters

Once approved, sponsors are able to approve vehicle dealerships they already work with that want to become speed limiter centres.

chunks.html_content: Contact the sponsors of your vehicle dealership to ask them if you can become a sponsored speed limiter centre.
chunks.plain_content:
Becoming a speed limiter centre
Get sponsored
Contact the sponsors of your vehicle dealership to ask them if you can become a sponsored speed limiter centre.

Becoming a speed limiter centre
Get sponsored
You can have more than 1 sponsor.

chunks.html_content:
Sponsors carry out regular checks on their approved agents equipment and also provide them with:

  • training
  • technical support
  • new equipment and software

chunks.html_content: You’ll receive an authorisation letter from your sponsor if they approve you as a sponsored speed limiter centre.
